The South African National Roads Agency ( SANRAL) has announced that toll fees on the countryâ€™s national roads will increase by just over 4.5%. The new tariffs will apply on the N3 toll road between Johannesburg and Durban, on the N4 between the Mozambican border and the Botswana border, as well as on the toll sections of the N1, N2, N17, N12, R30 and R21. The Swartruggens Plaza on the N4 has not been included in the increase.    